---
description: >
  Utility from `util-linux` that uses `seccomp` to selectively block
  system calls, then executes a command. New in Ubuntu 26.04+ (util-linux 2.40+).
functions:
  command:
    - description: Execute a command.
      code: enosys -- COMMAND
  shell:
    - description: Spawn a shell.
      code: enosys -- /bin/sh
  sudo:
    - description: If the binary is allowed to run as superuser by `sudo`, it does not drop the elevated privileges and may be used to access the file system, escalate or maintain privileged access.
      code: sudo enosys -- /bin/sh
---
